# Generated by Cargo
# will have compiled files and executables
debug
target

# These are backup files generated by rustfmt
**/*.rs.bk

# MSVC Windows builds of rustc generate these, which store debugging information
*.pdb

# Generated by cargo mutants
# Contains mutation testing data
**/mutants.out*/

# RustRover
#  JetBrains specific template is maintained in a separate JetBrains.gitignore that can
#  be found at https://github.com/github/gitignore/blob/main/Global/JetBrains.gitignore
#  and can be added to the global gitignore or merged into this file.  For a more nuclear
#  option (not recommended) you can uncomment the following to ignore the entire idea folder.
#.idea/

# claudebase: per-project ephemeral state (knowledge base + dev scratch)
# Pattern is `.claude/*` (NOT `.claude/`) so the negation below can re-include
# specific files — git's gitignore semantics forbid re-including a file whose
# PARENT DIRECTORY is excluded, so directory-form `.claude/` would block any
# `!.claude/...` negation. Listing the contents-form excludes everything
# inside .claude/ but leaves the directory itself visible to negations.
.claude/*
# ...except release-notes files, which release-engineer writes here and
# release.yml's body_path consumes at tag-checkout time to populate the
# GitHub Release body. Negation re-includes them while keeping all other
# .claude/ ephemera (plan, scratchpad, qa-evidence, knowledge/, *.db) ignored.
!.claude/release-notes-*.md
*.db
*.db-wal
*.db-shm

# claudebase: release-pipeline staging dir + local benchmark outputs
dist/
bench/reports/local-*.md
.DS_Store
